	<td>
		<h2>SPOJ Problem Set (classical)</h2>
				<h1>18175. TENNIS CHAMPIONSHIP</h1>
		<h2>Problem code: TENNIS1</h2>
	</td>
	</tr>
</table>

<p align="justify">
<p>N (2&lt;=N&lt;=10^18) players take part in tennis championship. In every match loser is out. Two players can play a game if in that moment the difference of played games of that two players is not more than 1. They are interested, how many matches will be in the champioship (maximal possible number) and what's the maximal possible number of games in which can take part the champion in that case.</p>
<h3>Input</h3>
<p>Single number N.</p>
<h3>Output</h3>
<p>Two numbers - answers to the questions.</p>
<h3>Example</h3>
<pre><strong>Input:</strong>
4

<strong>Output:</strong>
2 3
</pre>

